# LearnCraft LMS (Backend)

LearnCraft is a multi-tenant Learning Management System (LMS) backend built using NestJS, MongoDB, and JWT authentication.

The goal of this project is to simulate a real-world scalable backend system where instructors can create courses and students can enroll, learn, and track their progress.

---

## 🚀 Project Goals

This project is built to demonstrate:

- Scalable backend architecture using NestJS
- Authentication & Authorization (JWT-based)
- Role-based access control (Student, Instructor, Admin)
- Real-world database design using MongoDB
- Clean modular architecture
- System design thinking for production-level applications

---

## 🧠 Key Features

### 1. Authentication System
- User signup and login
- JWT-based authentication
- Secure password hashing using bcrypt
- Role-based access (student, instructor, admin)

---

### 2. Course Management
- Instructors can create courses
- Courses contain sections and lectures
- Draft and publish workflow for courses

---

### 3. Video Lecture System
- Video URLs stored in database
- Videos uploaded via cloud storage (e.g. Cloudinary)

---

### 4. Enrollment System
- Students can enroll in courses
- Access control based on enrollment

---

### 5. Reviews & Ratings
- Students can review courses
- Prevent duplicate reviews
- Maintain average rating and total reviews

---

### 6. User Roles & Approval System
- Users start as students by default
- Instructor role requires admin approval (via verification process)

---

### 7. Progress Tracking (Upcoming)
- Track lecture completion
- Resume learning from last watched position

---

## 🏗️ Tech Stack

- Backend: NestJS (Node.js framework)
- Database: MongoDB (Mongoose ORM)
- Authentication: JWT
- Password Security: bcrypt
- Validation: class-validator
- Configuration: @nestjs/config
- Storage (planned): Cloudinary

---

## 🧩 Architecture Overview

The project follows a modular architecture:

- **Controllers** → Handle HTTP requests
- **Services** → Business logic layer
- **Modules** → Feature-based separation (Auth, Users, Courses)
- **DTOs** → Input validation layer
- **Guards** → Authentication & role protection

---

## 📦 Core Modules

- Auth Module → Login, Signup, JWT handling
- User Module → User management and roles
- Course Module → Course creation and management
- Enrollment Module → Student course access
- Review Module → Ratings and feedback system

---

## 🔐 Security Design

- Passwords are hashed using bcrypt
- JWT used for stateless authentication
- Role-based access control (RBAC)
- Refresh token strategy (planned/optional enhancement)

---

## 🎯 Project Purpose

This project is NOT just a CRUD application.

It is designed to demonstrate:
- Real backend engineering skills
- System design understanding
- Scalable architecture thinking
- Production-level API design

